    Nun: (Gasps) It is done. My heart grows heavier, but your limbs are light again. Go... before I lose the strength to stand.
- "Why did the Church allow this?"
    Nun: We were terrified of the Dark. The High Priest said we had to 'Maintain the Altar.' He didn't tell us the Altar was a hydraulic piston. We betrayed the flock to save the Temple.
- "Where is the High Priest now?"
    Nun: He sits at the base of the Press, praying to the rhythm of the stamp. He believes the sound of crushing bone is the sound of God's forgiveness.